profileText: I have extensive experience in IT support as an IT technician at Amplius Field Service Group AB and as a laboratory assistant at ALS Danderyd. Additionally, I have worked in retail. Currently, I am studying Software Engineering and Management at the University of Gothenburg.

workExperienceItem.title: IT Technician, Amplius Field Service Group AB
workExperienceItem.text: As an IT technician, I was responsible for providing technical support and service to various clients. My role involved extensive fieldwork where I handled and resolved a variety of equipment, including Cisco devices, POS devices, and computers.

workExperienceItem.title: Laboratory Assistant, ALS Danderyd
workExperienceItem.text: Responsibilities included weighing soil samples, emptying sample vials, and washing various types of containers. I also had an additional responsibility as IT support, which involved tasks primarily related to the installation and troubleshooting of software, computers, and connected devices. Another major responsibility was key fob management.

workExperienceItem.title: Shop Assistant, Ica Stillingsön
workExperienceItem.text: Cashier service in an ICA store, mostly in a special department where garden products, toys, and home improvement products were sold. I also handled restocking of goods, cleaning, and weeding.

workExperienceItem.title: Leisure Assistant, Orust Municipality
workExperienceItem.text: Participated in the educational activities of the leisure center.

qualification: Experience in image and video editing

internshipItem.title: Shop Assistant, Ica Stillingsön
internshipItem.text: Assisted with general tasks in the store, primarily by unpacking and picking goods.
